{% extends "layouts/base.html.twig" %}

{% block title %}The Studio — Watch Minoo being built — Minoo{% endblock %}

{% block meta_description %}Watch Minoo being built, live, from inside Minoo. Russell streams the work from Sagamok Anishnawbek.{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <div class="content-well content-well--full">
    <div class="content-section flow-lg">
      <div>
        <h1>The Studio</h1>
        <p class="text-secondary">This is Minoo, being built. Right now, by Russell, from Sagamok Anishnawbek. Pull up a chair.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="live-embed">
        <div class="live-embed__player">
          <iframe
            src="https://player.twitch.tv/?channel=jonesrussell42&parent=minoo.live&parent=localhost"
            title="Twitch player — jonesrussell42"
            allowfullscreen
            loading="lazy"></iframe>
        </div>
        <div class="live-embed__chat">
          <iframe
            src="https://www.twitch.tv/embed/jonesrussell42/chat?parent=minoo.live&parent=localhost&darkpopout"
            title="Twitch chat — jonesrussell42"
            loading="lazy"></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>

      <section class="flow">
        <h2>What's happening here</h2>
        <p>Most build-in-public happens on someone else's platform. Twitter, YouTube, somewhere the audience lives but the work doesn't. This is the opposite: the build is happening inside the thing being built. The platform watches itself being made.</p>
        <p>If the stream is live above, you're watching me write the code that runs the page you're on right now. If it's offline, the player will tell you so — and you can <a href="https://www.twitch.tv/jonesrussell42" rel="noopener">follow on Twitch</a> to get pinged when it goes live again.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
